Nominated for 2 BAFTA Film Awards

In the slums of London before World War II, Tommy is an aimless teenager who tries to escape his squalid surroundings by entering a life of crime. He falls in with local racketeer Herbert Lom, who holds the rest of the slum citizens in a grip of fear. The film chronicles Tommy's sordid criminal progression.
